    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. The single gap — Test conditions at level 2 against a required level 3 — is acknowledged; the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol is accepted as sufficient for regulatory submission given the deterministic nature of the bench test and the pre-specified acceptance bounds. All three QoIs satisfy the <10% difference and E/uval <1.96 criteria. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion that the FEA framework adequately represents the compression-bending behavior of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
